A year after proposing a near-total ban on sales of products containing elephant ivory, the Obama administration made the rule final today, ending a trade as old as the United States.

Selling ivory is now prohibited, with few exceptions including musical instruments, furniture and items such as firearms containing fewer than 200 grams.
<div class="text_exposed_show">

We hope the latest ban by the Obama administration will act as a model for China to enact its own ban and ultimately end the worldwide trade in ivory.

